---
// Landing page — takes priority over Starlight's /docs/index.md
// because Astro pages dir route `/` wins over content collection

// This is a standalone page outside Starlight, so it does NOT get the
// `customCss` bundle that Starlight injects into docs pages — import it here.
import '../styles/custom.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Junando — Alert correlation and incident context delivery</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Junando correlates alerts from your observability stack and delivers actionable incident context directly to Slack or Teams." />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png" />
    <style is:global>
      /* Dark page base for the standalone landing: unlike Starlight docs pages,
         this page gets no framework-provided body background/color. */
      body {
        background: #0a0a0f;
        color: #e4e4e7;
        margin: 0;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="hero-badge">
          Open source · Apache 2.0
        </div>
        <h1>
          Alert correlation that<br />
          <span class="accent">actually helps at 3am</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="tagline">
          Junando correlates alerts from your observability stack and delivers actionable incident context directly to Slack or Teams.
        </p>
        <p class="value-prop">
          Instead of raw alerts flooding your channel at 3am, your team gets one structured message per incident with probable cause and recommended steps.
        </p>
        <p class="hero-meta">
          Built for engineering teams running multi-service observability stacks.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a href="/getting-started/" class="cta-primary">
            Get Started →
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/GerMoren/junando" class="cta-secondary">
            View on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-badges">
          <span class="hero-badge-small">
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z"/><path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"/><path d="M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
            Docker Compose ready
          </span>
          <span class="hero-badge-small">
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M9 19c-5 1.5-5-2.5-7-3m14 6v-3.87a3.37 3.37 0 0 0-.94-2.61c3.14-.35 6.44-1.54 6.44-7A5.44 5.44 0 0 0 20 4.77 5.07 5.07 0 0 0 19.91 1S18.73.65 16 2.48a13.38 13.38 0 0 0-7 0C6.27.65 5.09 1 5.09 1A5.07 5.07 0 0 0 5 4.77a5.44 5.44 0 0 0-1.5 3.78c0 5.42 3.3 6.61 6.44 7A3.37 3.37 0 0 0 9 18.13V22"/></svg>
            GitHub
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding:0 1.5rem;">
      <div class="features">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2a10 10 0 1 0 10 10H12V2z"/><path d="M12 2a10 10 0 0 1 10 10"/><path d="M12 12 4.35 6.75"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Zero mental load</h3>
          <p>LLM enrichment analyzes each incident and delivers probable cause with recommended steps — no more context switching.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M13 2 3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Easy to try</h3>
          <p>Docker Compose local setup gets the full stack running in minutes. Perfect for evaluation and development.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Open source</h3>
          <p>Apache 2.0 licensed. Deploy in your own AWS account with CDK — full control, no vendor lock-in.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mock-section">
      <div class="mock-section-header">
        <h2>What your team sees</h2>
        <p>One structured Slack message instead of a wall of alerts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mock-image-wrapper">
        <img src="/assets/slack-mock.svg" alt="Junando incident notification in Slack" />
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pipeline-section">
      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <p>From alert to actionable notification in seconds</p>
      <div style="display:flex;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <img src="/assets/pipeline-diagram.svg" alt="Junando pipeline: Ingest, Deduplicate, Enrich, Notify" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:1rem;" />
      </div>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:0.75rem;text-align:left;">
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-label">Step 1</div>
          <div class="step-title">Ingest</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Alerts arrive via webhook (Alertmanager-compatible)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-label">Step 2</div>
          <div class="step-title">Deduplicate</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Fingerprint-based clustering groups related alerts</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-label">Step 3</div>
          <div class="step-title">Enrich</div>
          <div class="step-desc">LLM analysis generates probable cause and recommendations</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-label">Step 4</div>
          <div class="step-title">Notify</div>
          <div class="step-desc">One structured message goes to Slack or Teams</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="trust-section">
      <div>
        <div class="trust-card">
          <div class="icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 22h20"/><path d="M15 10V5a3 3 0 0 0-3-3l-4 9v11h18"/><path d="M7 11v7"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Built for real production stacks</h3>
          <p>
            Designed for teams running tens to hundreds of services. Plugs into your existing Alertmanager, Grafana, and AWS infrastructure.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="trust-card">
          <div class="icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l7-4A2 2 0 0 0 21 16z"/><polyline points="3.27 6.96 12 12.01 20.73 6.96"/><line x1="12" y1="22.08" x2="12" y2="12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Bring your own LLM</h3>
          <p>
            Configurable LLM providers — OpenRouter, Gemini, Claude, or your own endpoint. Keep control over cost, latency, and data residency.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="final-cta">
      <h2>Ready to simplify your on-call experience?</h2>
      <p>
        Get started with Docker Compose in minutes. No credit card required — just your terminal.
      </p>
      <div class="final-cta-buttons">
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="cta-primary">
          Get Started →
        </a>
        <a href="/local-docker/" class="cta-secondary">
          Try Local Docker
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="https://github.com/GerMoren/junando">GitHub</a>
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="footer-docs-link">Docs</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/GerMoren/junando/blob/main/LICENSE">License</a>
      </div>
      <div class="copyright">
        Junando — Apache 2.0 licensed
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
